<h1><center>Iceland</center></h1>
<p><b>Iceland</b> is a country widely known as "the land of fire and ice," due to its combination of ice caps and active volcanoes. Reykjavik is the capital and largest city of Iceland.</p>
<br>
<div style="background-color: lightblue;"> 
<H4>Things to do in Iceland</H4>
<img src="Nlights.avif" alt="Northern lights" style="margin-left: 12px;"
width="440"
height="260"
<br>
<h4><i>Northern lights in Iceland</i></h4>
<p>Northern Lights (Aurora Borealis) in Iceland is that they are often referred to as the "Spectacular Dance of the Elves" in Icelandic folklore. In Icelandic mythology, it is believed that the Northern Lights are the result of the playful and mischievous activities of elves or hidden people in the night sky.</p>
<br>
<img src="golden circle.avif" alt="Golden Circle" style="margin-left: 12px;"
width="440"
height="260"
<br>
<h4><i>The Golden Circle</i></h4>
<p>The Golden Circle is a route that takes you to the most stunning and historically significant landmarks/places in Iceland. It's a circular route located in the southwestern part of Iceland, not far from Reykjavik.</p>
</div>
